Author: joe2x4#5987
Content:
```https://github.com/Mixa84/komodo/wiki/Pegs-CC```

In current peg system kmd 5% rewards are unavailable to user once kmd is locked for stable coin.

Is it possible or is there any benefit to allowing the stable coin creator to split and keep a portion of their locked kmd 5% reward if they take a reasonable loan of say 50% or less deposit for a long period of time. Ex: User gets  2.5% reward accruing per month for locking their kmd for a year, and creating stable coin from 50% of deposit, multisigners get the other 2.5%

Author: joe2x4#5987
Content: I guess what I'm trying to describe is a system for longer term loans that might compete against a shorter, potentially higher risk loan system. If it is just up to the cc pegs code then can't we expect to see different cc pegs modules with different loan terms ?

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: it would be very complicated, but maybe if there was a way to have a predefined percentage that is borrowed and also predefined term. so, ok, it is possible, but first we need to get the basic system working

Content: ELI5 how is komodo going to be quantum proof?

Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: https://komodoplatform.com/dilithium-quantum-secure-blockchain/

Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: > One of these modifications was to allow users to create a new type of quantum-secure address. First, users register a handle of their choosing. This registration process executes a transaction on the blockchain, which takes both the user‚Äôs quantum-secured blockchain public key and chosen handle into account. This allows a mere 32 bytes of data (the transaction ID of the registration transaction) to refer to 3 kilobytes of data (the uncompressed Dilithium public key).

Content:
Should you want more detail, check these out:
